Question

 

Select the best answer. Who is NOT considered a worker?

Your answer:

Correct answer: A visitor to the workplace

Question

 

As an employee or other worker, you have the duty to…

Your answer:

Correct answer: … take reasonable care of your own health and safety as well as all others at the workplace

Question

 

As an employee, or other type of worker, you can personally be prosecuted if you are involved in a breach of WHS laws. True or false?

Your answer:

Correct answer: True

Question

 

How can you help minimise WHS risks at work?

Your answer:

Correct answer: All of the above

Question

 

Jim works as a glass fitter. While at work, he notices some broken glass on the floor. What should he do?

Your answer:

Correct answer: Immediately clean up the broken glass (or tell someone else about it)

Question

 

You notice a potential danger at your workplace. Should you try to reduce, isolate or remove the hazard yourself first?

Your answer:

Correct answer: Yes, although sometimes it may be better to tell someone about it

Question

 

When may you cease or refuse to carry out work?

Your answer:

Correct answer: Only if you have a reasonable concern that the work would expose you to a serious risk to your health or safety

Question

 

Complete the sentence. If a worker refuses to carry out work, they must…

Your answer:

Correct answer: … notify the PCBU as soon as practicable and carry out any alternative work that is safe and appropriate

Question

 

What are the major types of prohibited conduct under the WHS Act?

Your answer:

Correct answer: Coercion, misrepresentation, discrimination

Question

 

Complete the sentence. A supervisor acts in a discriminatory way if they…

Your answer:

Correct answer: … offer a job to a prospective worker on worse terms than the terms offered to others

Question

 

Complete the sentence. It is prohibited to discriminate against a person who…

Your answer:

Correct answer: All of the above

Question

 

A PCBU threatens to dismiss an employee if they exercise a power under the WHS Act. Is this a type of prohibited conduct?

Your answer:

Correct answer: Yes, it is coercion

Question

 

A PCBU knowingly misleads one of his employees by giving him false information about his rights under the WHS Act. What type of prohibited conduct is this?

Your answer:

Correct answer: Misrepresentation

Question

 

A manager notices an electrical outlet is faulty. He knows this will expose workers to a risk of serious injury or death but does nothing to resolve the situation. What type of offence is this?

Your answer:

Correct answer: Category 1 offence

Question

 

A supervisor fails to fulfil her health and safety duty but this failure does not expose the individual to whom the duty is owed to a risk of death or serious injury. What type of offence is this?

Your answer:

Correct answer: Category 3 offence
